vectorData.altText: 7. A nerve contains sympathetic postganglionic fibres. What nerve might it be? Choose all that apply.

That's right!  Sympathetic postganglionic fibres destined to innervate targets in the body wall pass from the chain ganglion through the grey ramus communicans, spinal nerve, and then either the dorsal or ventral ramus to reach their target tissue.
